message.content:
A 'boxer' is a person who practices the sport of boxing, typically in a professional or amateur competitive setting. 
Boxers typically wear padded gloves and engage in hand-to-hand combat within a designated ring. 
The physical appearance of a boxer is often characterized by muscular development and a lean, athletic build. 
Boxers may have scars or other visible marks on their face or body as a result of their sport. 
Boxing is often associated with aggression and fighting, although some boxers may participate for non-violent reasons such as fitness or recreation. 
Boxing matches can be found in a variety of settings, from small local gyms to large arenas and pay-per-view events. 
Overall, the visual characteristics of a boxer suggest strength, athleticism, and a willingness to engage in physical challenge.
